KKR Leads Investment in Magma Fincorp of India, Buys Ipreo

-- B y   J a s o n   K e l l y
-- 
2011-05-23T17:04:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/kkr-leads-investment-in-magma-fincorp-of-india-buys-ipreo.html
KKR & Co. led a 4.4 billion rupee
($97.3 million) investment in  Magma Fincorp Ltd. (MGMA)  of India and
acquired Ipreo Holdings LLC in separate private-equity
transactions targeting the financial-services industry.  KKR teamed with International Finance Corp. to provide
capital to Mumbai-based Magma, a commercial lender, the
companies said today in a statement. International Finance,
affiliated with the Washington-based World Bank, finances
private-sector investments in developing countries.  Ipreo Holdings, based in New York, operates the Bigdough
database of institutional investors. New York-based KKR said it
bought the company from private-equity firm Veronis Suhler
Stevenson for an undisclosed amount.  KKR also said today it hired  Hewlett-Packard Co. (HPQ)  senior
vice president Marius Haas as an industry adviser to work with
the firm’s technology team. Haas, who started his career with
 Intel Corp. (INTC) , worked at Compaq Computer Corp. before joining  Palo
Alto , California-based Hewlett-Packard, where he also led the
company’s mergers and acquisition efforts among other positions,
according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Kelly in New York at 
